Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce. Place @wooden skewers{8} in a #shallow dish{} and cover with water to soak.

Peel @garlic{3%cloves}; thinly slice one clove (two cloves for 4 servings). Mince remaining garlic. Halve @mini cucumber{2} lengthwise; slice into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Roughly chop @peanuts{1%ounce}. Roughly chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}, reserving 2-3 whole sprigs for garnish.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Place shrimp in a #medium bowl{}. Add half the @Omsom Vietnamese Lemongrass BBQ Marinade{1} and @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and toss to combine.

Pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with paper towels. Cut steak into 1-inch cubes. Season all over with salt and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add minced garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{¾%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Cucumber Salad ==

In a second medium bowl, combine cucumber, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, two packets of @rice wine vinegar{5%tablespoon} (four packets for 4 servings), @sugar{2.5%tsp} (3 tsp for 4), and a pinch of salt. Stir to coat; set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

== Shrimp Skewers ==

Thread marinated shrimp onto skewers (4-5 shrimp per skewer); discard marinade in bowl.

Place shrimp skewers on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Roast on top rack for ~{4%minutes}.

Remove from oven and spoon remaining Omsom Vietnamese Lemongrass BBQ Marinade over skewers.

Return to top rack and roast until shrimp are opaque and fully cooked, ~{4-5%minutes} more.

> GRILL PAN ALTERNATIVE: Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #grill pan{} over medium-high heat. Add shrimp skewers; cook until shrimp begin to brown, 2-3 minutes. Flip, then brush with remaining lemongrass marinade. Cook until opaque and fully cooked, 2-3 minutes more.

== Shaking Beef ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring, until beginning to brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Push to one side of pan.

Heat another drizzle of oil in empty side of pan. Add steak cubes and sear until beginning to brown on one side, ~{2-3%minutes} (stir onion occasionally as you sear beef). Flip steak cubes and cook ~{1%minute} more.

Add sliced garlic, @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, and remaining vinegar; stir entire contents of pan to combine. Cook until steak is cooked to desired doneness, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season to taste with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Divide rice between plates.

> TIP: To get a perfect mound of rice, spray the insides of two small bowls with nonstick spray and pack with rice. Carefully invert bowls onto plates and slowly lift bowls away.

Top rice with beef. Serve cucumber salad and shrimp skewers alongside rice and beef. Garnish with peanuts, chopped cilantro, and whole cilantro sprigs.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.